 theoretical purposes, among them:Characterisation of texts by means of parameters (measures, indicators) as taken from established mathematical statistics or specifically constructed ones in individual cases.Comparison of texts on the basis of their quantitative characteristics and classification of the texts by the results.Research for the laws of text, which control the mechanisms connected to text creation. As a remote aim, the construction of a theory of text consisting of a system of text laws. The final attempt of every possible quantitative text analysis is the construction of a text theory. The book illustrates this on examples of such laws and corresponding empirical tests.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aLinguisticsxMethodology. 0aLinguisticsxStatistical methods. 0aRepetition (Rhetoric) 0aRepetition (Rhetoric). 0aWritingxMathematical models 0aWritingxMathematical models. 4aquantitative linguistics, repetition analysis. 4aquantitative text analysis, statistical methodology. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aKöhler, Reinhard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2015z9783110438710oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831104120240 cprintz978311041179940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311041194240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110411942423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110411942.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHAL